Where is how it works
git bisect is a binary search through your commit history to find the exact commit that introduced a bug.

The core idea
You tell git two things:

a bad commit (where the bug exists — usually HEAD)
a good commit (where everything worked — some point in the past)
Git then checks out the commit exactly halfway between them and asks: good or bad? You test, answer, and it halves the search space again. Repeat until it pinpoints the culprit.

